  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "\"Fair-AI methods and resources\", bias mitigation can happen in multiple crucial stages, including data processing approaches (pre-processing), specialized fair-AI algorithms (in-processing), and model sanitization (postprocessing).",
    "The effectiveness of mitigations at those stages presents some challenges.",
    "Pre-processing approaches may inadvertently remove relevant or informative data, with the risk of overgeneralizing and ignoring legitimate differences that may exist among subgroups.",
    "This is a problem shared with the data processing for privacy-enforcement (Shahriar et al., 2023).",
    "In-processing approaches follow the optimization of some trade-off between performance and fairness metrics."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This is a problem shared with the data processing for privacy-enforcement (Shahriar et al., 2023)."
  ]
}